\subsection{Greenhouse gas emissions}
%++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Globally, food and land use account for 23\% of GHG emissions~\cite{IPCC:2018aa}.
\index{greenhouse gases}
Tropical rainforest deforestation, particularly in Brazil and Indonesia,
contributes significantly to global GHG emissions.
In the U.S., soil management accounts for over half of agricultural GHG emissions~\cite{USEPA:2021uj}.
Over-application of synthetic nitrogen-based fertilizers releases significant
amounts of N$_2$O, a very potent GHG.
The paragraphs below look at two very important greenhouse gases, carbon
dioxide~(CO$_2$) and methane~(CH$_4$).

